question: Will the Hurricanes be the 2023 NHL Champion?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if the Carolina Hurricanes become the 2023 Stanley Cup Champion. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

If it is determined at any point that it is impossible for the Hurricanes to be the 2023 Stanley Cup Champion based on the rules of the NHL (e.g. they're eliminated in the playoffs), this market will immediately resolve to "No."

If this team is still in contention to become the champion and the champion still isn't determined by November 3, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET, this market will resolve 50-50.

question: Will Ron DeSantis file to run for president by May 31, 2023?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if by May 31, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET, Ronald Dion DeSantis or his authorized representative does at least one of the following: 
-Files a Statement of Candidacy for the office of President of the United States in the 2024 election with the Federal Election Commission (FEC) 
-Amends an existing Statement of Candidacy for the office of President of the United States in the 2024 election with the FEC 
-Designates a principal campaign committee for the office of President of the United States in the 2024 election 
-Otherwise files or communicates with the FEC with the same effect as the filing of a Form 2 Statement of Candidacy for the 2024 election. 

Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

Please note that any informal declarations by Ron DeSantis and/or his representatives regarding DeSantis's intentions to run will have no bearing on this market; only the above criteria will be used to resolve this market. This market will resolve based on the official FEC website (https://www.fec.gov/), however a consensus of credible reporting will suffice.

question: League of Legends: Will a South Korean team win The 2023 Mid-Season Invitational?
description:
The Mid-Season Invitational (MSI) is an annual Riot Games-organized tournament for League of Legends, a multiplayer online battle arena video game. It is the second most important international League of Legends tournament, behind only the World Championship. The 2023 Mid-Season Invitational will be held from May 2 to 21, 2023, in the Copper Box Arena in London, UK. 

This market will resolve to "Yes" if a team from South Korea wins The 2023 MSI tournament and to "No" otherwise. If all South Korean teams are removed from contention the market may immediately resolve to "No."

This market will resolve according to official information from Riot Games, the tournament's organizer, either from their website (https://lolesports.com/) or Twitter profiles (https://twitter.com/LeagueOfLegends, https://twitter.com/riotgames), however a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.
